717    x[1] = x[2];



718    x[2] = absx11;



719    absx11 = x[4];



720    x[4] = x[5];



721    x[5] = absx11;



722    absx11 = x[7];



723    x[7] = x[8];



724    x[8] = absx11;



725  }



726



727  x[5] /= x[4];



728  x[8] -= x[5] * x[7];



729  absx11 = (x[5] * x[1] - x[2]) / x[8];



730  absx21 = -(x[7] * absx11 + x[1]) / x[4];



731  y[p1 + 1] = ((1.0 - x[3] * absx21) - x[6] * absx11) / x[0];



732  y[p1 + 2] = absx21;



733  y[p1 + 3] = absx11;



734  absx11 = -x[5] / x[8];



735  absx21 = (1.0 - x[7] * absx11) / x[4];



736  y[p2] = -(x[3] * absx21 + x[6] * absx11) / x[0];



737  y[p2 + 1] = absx21;



738  y[p2 + 2] = absx11;



739  absx11 = 1.0 / x[8];



740  absx21 = -x[7] * absx11 / x[4];



741  y[p3] = -(x[3] * absx21 + x[6] * absx11) / x[0];



742  y[p3 + 1] = absx21;



743  y[p3 + 2] = absx11;



744}

1057  /* Update the flag to indicate when data transfers from

1064  /* Logic: '<S2>/Logical Operator' incorporates:



1065   *  Inport: '<Root>/MT_valid'



1066   */



1067  rtb_LogicalOperator_m = (rtU.MT_valid[0] && rtU.MT_valid[1] && rtU.MT_valid[2]);



1068



1069  /* MATLAB Function: '<S115>/time-conversion-lib' incorporates:



1070   *  Constant: '<S67>/dut1'



1071   *  Inport: '<Root>/GPS_time'



1072   */



1073  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1074  /*  Husky-Sat 1, ADCS Subsystem */



1075  /*   */



1076  /*  Convert a GPS time into date-time, Julian date and Julian century in the */



1077  /*  UT1 and TT frames. Accounts for leap seconds. */



1078  /*  */



1079  /*    dUT1 obtained from: */



1080  /*        http://maia.usno.navy.mil/ser7/finals.daily */



1081  /*  */



1082  /*  T. Reynolds -- 2.28.18 */



1083  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1084  /*  #codegen */



1085  /* MATLAB Function 'time_conversion_lib/time-conversion-lib': '<S117>:1' */



1086  /*  Constants */



1087  /* '<S117>:1:16' dAT         = 37.0; */



1088  /*  From MJD 58158 (Feb 7, 2018) */



1089  /* '<S117>:1:17' gps2tai     = 19.0; */



1090  /*  From MJD 58158 */



1091  /* '<S117>:1:18' gps2tt      = 32.184 + gps2tai; */



1092  /* '<S117>:1:19' gps2utc     = gps2tai - dAT; */



1093  /* '<S117>:1:20' gps2ut1     = gps2tai - dAT + dUT1; */



1094  /* '<S117>:1:21' sec2day     = 1/86400; */



1095  /* '<S117>:1:22' week2day    = 7; */



1096  /* '<S117>:1:23' JD_GPSepoch = 2444244.5; */



1097  /* '<S117>:1:24' JD_J2000    = 2451545.0; */



1098  /* '<S117>:1:25' JD2cent     = 1/36525; */



1099  /* '<S117>:1:27' sec_in = cur_gps(1); */



1100  /* '<S117>:1:27' week_in = cur_gps(2); */



1101  /*  --------------------------- % */



1102  /*  Translate GPS w-s to JD and Gregorian ymd-hms */



1103  /* '<S117>:1:31' JD_days_gps     = JD_GPSepoch + week2day*week_in + sec2day*sec_in; */



1104  JD_days_gps = (7.0 * rtU.GPS_time[1] + 2.4442445E+6) + 1.1574074074074073E-5 *



1105    rtU.GPS_time[0];



1106



1107  /* '<S117>:1:32' JD_utc          = JD_days_gps + sec2day*gps2utc; */



1108  /* '<S117>:1:33' JD_ut1          = JD_days_gps + sec2day*gps2ut1; */



1109  rtb_TrigonometricFunction1_o1 = JD_days_gps + -0.00020759027777777776;



1110



1111  /* '<S117>:1:34' JD_TT           = JD_days_gps + sec2day*gps2tt; */



1112  /* '<S117>:1:36' JD_utc_J2000    = JD_utc - JD_J2000; */



1113  /* '<S117>:1:37' JD_ut1_J2000    = JD_ut1 - JD_J2000; */



1114  /* '<S117>:1:38' T_ut1_J2000     = JD_ut1_J2000*JD2cent; */



1115  rtb_T_ut1_J2000 = ((JD_days_gps + -0.00020759027777777776) - 2.451545E+6) *



1116    2.7378507871321012E-5;



1117



1118  /* '<S117>:1:39' T_TT_J2000      = JD2cent*( JD_TT - JD_J2000 ); */



1119  rtb_T_TT_J2000 = ((JD_days_gps + 0.00059240740740740738) - 2.451545E+6) *



1120    2.7378507871321012E-5;



1121



1122  /* MATLAB Function: '<S66>/MATLAB Function' */



1123  /* '<S117>:1:41' time_ut1 = JD_2_ymdhms( JD_ut1 ); */



1124  /*  This algorithm is based on Vallado 4e algorithm 22, pp 202. */



1125  /*  Constants */



1126  /* '<S117>:1:49' JD_1900     = 2415019.5; */



1127  /* '<S117>:1:50' Lmonth      = [31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31]; */



1128  /*  Convert JD to date-time */



1129  /* '<S117>:1:53' T1900   = (JD - JD_1900)/365.25; */



1130  /*  base epoch is 1900 */



1131  /* '<S117>:1:54' year    = 1900 + floor(T1900); */



1132  /* '<S117>:1:56' leapyrs = floor((year - 1900 - 1)*0.25); */



1133  /* '<S117>:1:57' days    = (JD - JD_1900) - ((year - 1900)*365 + leapyrs ); */



1134  /* '<S117>:1:59' if days < 1 */



1135  /* '<S117>:1:65' if mod(year,4) == 0 */



1136  /* '<S117>:1:69' dayofyear   = floor(days); */



1137  /* '<S117>:1:71' day     = 0; */



1138  /* '<S117>:1:72' month   = 0; */



1139  /* '<S117>:1:74' while day < dayofyear */



1140  /* dayofmonth = dayofyear - (day - Lmonth(month)); */



1141  /* '<S117>:1:81' tau     = 24*( days-dayofyear ); */



1142  /* '<S117>:1:82' hour    = floor( tau ); */



1143  /* '<S117>:1:83' min     = floor( 60*(tau - hour) ); */



1144  /* '<S117>:1:84' sec     = 3600*( tau - hour - (min/60) ); */



1145  /* '<S117>:1:86' time    = [ year, month, dayofyear, hour, min, sec ]; */



1146  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1147  /*  UW HuskySat-1, ADCS Team */



1148  /*  Algorithm to find the sun vector in the ECI frame. Based on algorithm 29  */



1149  /*    from Vallado 4e (pp. 279-280). */



1150  /*  */



1151  /*  T. Reynolds -- 2.23.18 */



1152  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1153  /* MATLAB Function 'sun_vector_lib/MATLAB Function': '<S112>:1' */



1154  /*  Constants */



1155  /* '<S112>:1:11' AU2KM   = 149597870.700; */



1156  /* '<S112>:1:12' DEG2RAD     = pi/180.0; */



1157  /* '<S112>:1:13' TWOPI   = 2*pi; */



1158  /*  Mean longitude in a mean-equator of date frame */



1159  /* '<S112>:1:16' mean_long_sun  = rem(280.460 + 36000.771*JD_cent_ut1,360); */



1160  /*  [deg] */



1161  /*  Mean anomaly for the sun. Low precision formula since we're approximating */



1162  /*  T_TDB with T_UT1. */



1163  /* '<S112>:1:20' mean_anom_sun       = rem(357.5291092 + 35999.05034*JD_cent_ut1,360); */



1164  /* [deg] */



1165  /* '<S112>:1:21' mean_anom_sun_rad   = mod(DEG2RAD*mean_anom_sun,TWOPI); */



1166  mean_anom_sun_rad = rt_remd_snf(35999.05034 * rtb_T_ut1_J2000 + 357.5291092,



1167    360.0) * 0.017453292519943295 / 6.2831853071795862;



1168  if (fabs(mean_anom_sun_rad - rt_roundd_snf(mean_anom_sun_rad)) <=



1169      2.2204460492503131E-16 * fabs(mean_anom_sun_rad)) {



1170    mean_anom_sun_rad = 0.0;



1171  } else {



1172    mean_anom_sun_rad = (mean_anom_sun_rad - floor(mean_anom_sun_rad)) *



1173      6.2831853071795862;



1174  }



1175



1176  /*  Approximate the ecliptic longitude of the sun */



1177  /* '<S112>:1:24' long_eclp       = mean_long_sun + 1.914666471*sin(mean_anom_sun_rad) + ... */



1178  /* '<S112>:1:25'                     0.019994643*sin(2*mean_anom_sun_rad); */



1179  /* [deg] */



1180  /* '<S112>:1:26' long_eclp       = rem(DEG2RAD*long_eclp,360); */



1181  /*  [rad]    */



1182  /* '<S112>:1:27' long_eclp_rad   = mod(DEG2RAD*long_eclp,TWOPI); */



1183  long_eclp_rad = rt_remd_snf(((rt_remd_snf(36000.771 * rtb_T_ut1_J2000 + 280.46,



1184    360.0) + 1.914666471 * sin(mean_anom_sun_rad)) + sin(2.0 * mean_anom_sun_rad)



1185    * 0.019994643) * 0.017453292519943295, 360.0) * 0.017453292519943295 /



1186    6.2831853071795862;



1187  if (fabs(long_eclp_rad - rt_roundd_snf(long_eclp_rad)) <=



1188      2.2204460492503131E-16 * fabs(long_eclp_rad)) {



1189    long_eclp_rad = 0.0;



1190  } else {



1191    long_eclp_rad = (long_eclp_rad - floor(long_eclp_rad)) * 6.2831853071795862;



1192  }



1193



1194  /*  Assume the ecliptic latitude is zero */



1195  /* '<S112>:1:30' lat_eclp     = 0; */



1196  /* [deg] */



1197  /*  Approximate the obliquity of the ecliptic using */



1198  /* '<S112>:1:33' oblq        = 23.439291 - 0.0130042*JD_cent_ut1; */



1199  /* '<S112>:1:34' oblq_rad    = DEG2RAD*oblq; */



1200  oblq_rad = (23.439291 - 0.0130042 * rtb_T_ut1_J2000) * 0.017453292519943295;



1201



1202  /*  Find the distance in AU from E to S */



1203  /* '<S112>:1:37' r           =  1.000140612 - 0.016708617*cos(mean_anom_sun_rad) - ... */



1204  /* '<S112>:1:38'                     0.000139589*cos(2*mean_anom_sun_rad); */



1205  mean_anom_sun_rad = (1.000140612 - 0.016708617 * cos(mean_anom_sun_rad)) - cos



1206    (2.0 * mean_anom_sun_rad) * 0.000139589;



1207



1208  /* '<S112>:1:39' x_MOD_km    = r*cos(long_eclp_rad)*AU2KM; */

1210  /* '<S112>:1:41' z_MOD_km    = r*sin(oblq_rad)*sin(long_eclp_rad)*AU2KM; */



1211  /* '<S112>:1:43' sun_vector_mod_km = [x_MOD_km; y_MOD_km; z_MOD_km]; */



1212  /*  Convert to ECI (mean-equator-mean-equinox) frame  */



1213  /* '<S112>:1:46' sun_vector_eci_km   = mod2eci(sun_vector_mod_km,JD_cent_ut1); */



1214  /* '<S112>:1:52' [prec,~,~,~,~] = precess ( JD_cent_ut1 ); */



1215  /*  " to rad */



1216  /* '<S112>:1:60' convrt = pi / (180.0*3600.0); */



1217  /*  ------------------ iau 03 precession angles ------------------- */



1218  /* '<S112>:1:63' oblo =  84381.406; */



1219  /*  " */



1220  /* '<S112>:1:64' psia =  (((( -0.0000000951 * ttt + 0.000132851 ) * ttt - 0.00114045 ) *... */

1258  s = sin(-c);

1266  /* '<S112>:1:88' a5  = rot1mat(wa); */



1267  /*  precess */

1269  b_s = sin(b_c);



1270



1271  /* '<S112>:1:98' c   = cos( x_rad ); */



1272  b_c = cos(b_c);



1273



1274  /* '<S112>:1:100' DCMx    = [ 1   0   0 */



1275  /* '<S112>:1:101'             0   c   s; */



1276  /* '<S112>:1:102'             0  -s   c ]; */



1277  /* '<S112>:1:89' a6  = rot3mat(psia); */



1278  /* '<S112>:1:108' s   = sin( z_rad ); */



1279  c_s = sin(c_c);



1280



1281  /* '<S112>:1:109' c   = cos( z_rad ); */



1282  c_c = cos(c_c);

1285  /* '<S112>:1:112'            -s   c   0; */



1286  /* '<S112>:1:113'             0   0   1 ]; */

1291  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[0] = c_c;



1292  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[3] = c_s;



1293  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[6] = 0.0;

1295  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[4] = c_c;



1296  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[7] = 0.0;

1298  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[5] = 0.0;



1299  rtb_mod_to_gcrf[8] = 1.0;



1300  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {

1312  b_2[4] = b_c;



1313  b_2[7] = b_s;



1314  b_2[2] = 0.0;

1438  /* '<S116>:1:70' 37  0   0   0   2   0   63      0.0     -2      0.0 */



1439  /* '<S116>:1:71' 40  -1  0   2   2   2   -59     0.0     26      0.0 */



1440  /* '<S116>:1:72' 39  -1  0   0   0   1   -58     -0.1    32      0.0 */



1441  /* '<S116>:1:73' 41  1   0   2   0   1   -51     0.0     27      0.0 */

1444  /* '<S116>:1:76' 42  0   0   2   2   2   -38     0.0     16      0.0 */



1445  /* '<S116>:1:77' 45  2   0   2   0   2   -31     0.0     13      0.0 */



1446  /* '<S116>:1:78' 43  2   0   0   0   0   29      0.0     -1      0.0 */



1447  /* '<S116>:1:79' 44  1   0   2   -2  2   29      0.0     -12     0.0 */



1448  /* '<S116>:1:80' 46  0   0   2   0   0   26      0.0     -1      0.0 */



1449  /* '<S116>:1:81' 15  0   0   2   -2  0   -22     0.0     0       0.0 */



1450  /* '<S116>:1:82' 47  -1  0   2   0   1   21      0.0     -10     0.0 */



1451  /* '<S116>:1:83' 16  0   2   0   0   0   17      -0.1    0       0.0 */

1453  /* '<S116>:1:85' 48  -1  0   0   2   1   16      0.0     -8      0.0 ... */



1454  /* '<S116>:1:86' ]; */



1455  /*  Map coefficients to radians (this should be embedded in the data) */



1456  /*  nc(:,end-3:end) = nc(:,end-3:end) * 0.0001 * asec2rad; */



1457  /*  Compute nutation in longitude (psi), and latitude (eps) */



1458  /* '<S116>:1:92' dpsi_1980 = 0; */



1459  c = 0.0;



1460



1461  /* '<S116>:1:92' deps_1980 = 0; */



1462  b_s = 0.0;



1463



1464  /* '<S116>:1:93' for i = 1:size(nc,1) */



1465  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 30; idx2++) {



1466    /* '<S116>:1:94' api         =   nc(i,2) * M_moon + nc(i,3) * M_sun + nc(i,4) * u_moon + nc(i,5) * D_sun + nc(i,6) * O_moon; */



1467    c_s = (((nc[30 + idx2] * b_c + nc[60 + idx2] * c_c) + nc[90 + idx2] *



1468            oblq_rad) + nc[120 + idx2] * s) + nc[150 + idx2] * mean_anom_sun_rad;



1469

1471    c += (nc[210 + idx2] * rtb_T_TT_J2000 + nc[180 + idx2]) * 0.0001 * sin(c_s);



1472



1473    /* '<S116>:1:96' deps_1980   =   0.0001 * (nc(i,9) + nc(i,10) * jd_tt_j2000_century) * cos(api) + deps_1980; */



1474    b_s += (nc[270 + idx2] * rtb_T_TT_J2000 + nc[240 + idx2]) * 0.0001 * cos(c_s);



1475  }



1476



1477  /* '<S116>:1:99' eps_1980 = epsb_1980 + asec2rad * deps_1980; */



1478  c_c = 4.84813681109536E-6 * b_s + long_eclp_rad;



1479



1480  /* '<S116>:1:100' tod_to_mod = rot1(-epsb_1980) * rot3(asec2rad * dpsi_1980) * rot1(eps_1980); */



1481  /* '<S116>:1:149' y = [1 0 0; 0 cos(u) sin(u); 0 -sin(u) cos(u)]; */



1482  b_c = 4.84813681109536E-6 * c;



1483



1484  /* '<S116>:1:157' y = [cos(u) sin(u) 0; -sin(u) cos(u) 0; 0 0 1]; */



1485  /* '<S116>:1:149' y = [1 0 0; 0 cos(u) sin(u); 0 -sin(u) cos(u)]; */



1486  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[1] = 0.0;



1487  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[4] = cos(-long_eclp_rad);



1488  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[7] = sin(-long_eclp_rad);



1489  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[2] = 0.0;



1490  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[5] = -sin(-long_eclp_rad);



1491  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[8] = cos(-long_eclp_rad);



1492  rtb_MatrixMultiply[0] = cos(b_c);



1493  rtb_MatrixMultiply[3] = sin(b_c);



1494  rtb_MatrixMultiply[6] = 0.0;



1495  rtb_MatrixMultiply[1] = -sin(b_c);



1496  rtb_MatrixMultiply[4] = cos(b_c);



1497  rtb_MatrixMultiply[7] = 0.0;



1498  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[0] = 1.0;



1499  rtb_MatrixMultiply[2] = 0.0;



1500  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[3] = 0.0;



1501  rtb_MatrixMultiply[5] = 0.0;



1502  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[6] = 0.0;



1503  rtb_MatrixMultiply[8] = 1.0;



1504  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {

1506      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] = 0.0;

1508        rtb_teme_to_gcrf[idx2];



1509      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] += rtb_MatrixMultiply[3 * sigIdx + 1] *



1510        rtb_teme_to_gcrf[idx2 + 3];



1511      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] += rtb_MatrixMultiply[3 * sigIdx + 2] *



1512        rtb_teme_to_gcrf[idx2 + 6];



1513    }



1514



1515    a_2[3 * idx2] = c_0[idx2];



1516  }



1517



1518  a_2[1] = 0.0;



1519  a_2[4] = cos(c_c);



1520  a_2[7] = sin(c_c);



1521  a_2[2] = 0.0;



1522  a_2[5] = -sin(c_c);



1523  a_2[8] = cos(c_c);

1525  /*  Generate Precession matrix */



1526  /* '<S116>:1:103' zeta    =   asec2rad * (2306.2181 * jd_tt_j2000_century + 0.30188 * jd_tt_j2000_century^2 + 0.017998 * jd_tt_j2000_century^3); */



1527  b_c = ((rtb_T_TT_J2000 * rtb_T_TT_J2000 * 0.30188 + 2306.2181 * rtb_T_TT_J2000)



1528         + 0.017998 * rt_powd_snf(rtb_T_TT_J2000, 3.0)) * 4.84813681109536E-6;

1539                      (rtb_T_TT_J2000, 3.0)) * 4.84813681109536E-6);

1542  /* '<S116>:1:157' y = [cos(u) sin(u) 0; -sin(u) cos(u) 0; 0 0 1]; */



1543  rtb_MatrixMultiply[0] = cos(b_c);



1544  rtb_MatrixMultiply[3] = sin(b_c);



1545  rtb_MatrixMultiply[6] = 0.0;



1546  rtb_MatrixMultiply[1] = -sin(b_c);



1547  rtb_MatrixMultiply[4] = cos(b_c);



1548  rtb_MatrixMultiply[7] = 0.0;



1549  rtb_teme_to_gcrf[0] = cos(rtb_T_TT_J2000);

1552  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {

1571  b_2[6] = 0.0;



1572  b_2[1] = -sin(c_c);



1573  b_2[4] = cos(c_c);



1574  b_2[7] = 0.0;



1575  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {

1584    }

1587  }

1589  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {



1590    for (sigIdx = 0; sigIdx < 3; sigIdx++) {



1591      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] = 0.0;

1593      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] += b_2[3 * idx2 + 1] * a_2[sigIdx + 3];



1594      rtb_mod_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] += b_2[3 * idx2 + 2] * a_2[sigIdx + 6];



1595    }



1596  }

1598  /*  Compute equation of Equinoxes */



1599  /* '<S116>:1:110' eqe_1980 = asec2rad * (dpsi_1980  * cos(epsb_1980) + 0.00264 * sin(O_moon) + 0.000063 * sin(2 * O_moon)); */



1600  rtb_T_TT_J2000 = ((c * cos(long_eclp_rad) + 0.00264 * sin(mean_anom_sun_rad))



1601                    + sin(2.0 * mean_anom_sun_rad) * 6.3E-5) *



1602    4.84813681109536E-6;



1603



1604  /* '<S116>:1:111' teme_to_tod = rot3(-eqe_1980); */



1605  /* '<S116>:1:157' y = [cos(u) sin(u) 0; -sin(u) cos(u) 0; 0 0 1]; */



1606  /*  % Compute sidereal rotation */



1607  /*  GMST_1982 = asec2rad * (67310.54841 ... */



1608  /*                          + (876600 * 3600 + 8640184.812866) * jd_ut1_j2000_century ... */



1609  /*                          + 0.093104 * jd_ut1_j2000_century^2 ... */



1610  /*                          - 6.2e-6 * jd_ut1_j2000_century^3); */



1611  /* '<S116>:1:118' GMST_1982 = (67310.54841 ... */



1612  /* '<S116>:1:119'                         + (876600 * 3600 + 8640184.812866) * jd_ut1_j2000_century ... */



1613  /* '<S116>:1:120'                         + 0.093104 * jd_ut1_j2000_century^2 ... */

1615  rtb_T_ut1_J2000 = ((3.1644001848128662E+9 * rtb_T_ut1_J2000 + 67310.54841) +



1616                     rtb_T_ut1_J2000 * rtb_T_ut1_J2000 * 0.093104) - 6.2E-6 *



1617    rt_powd_snf(rtb_T_ut1_J2000, 3.0);



1618



1619  /* '<S116>:1:122' GMST_1982 = mod(GMST_1982,sign(GMST_1982)*86400) / 240; */



1620  if (rtb_T_ut1_J2000 < 0.0) {



1621    long_eclp_rad = -1.0;



1622  } else if (rtb_T_ut1_J2000 > 0.0) {



1623    long_eclp_rad = 1.0;



1624  } else if (rtb_T_ut1_J2000 == 0.0) {



1625    long_eclp_rad = 0.0;



1626  } else {



1627    long_eclp_rad = rtb_T_ut1_J2000;



1628  }



1629



1630  mean_anom_sun_rad = long_eclp_rad * 86400.0;



1631  if (!(mean_anom_sun_rad == 0.0)) {



1632    if (mean_anom_sun_rad == mean_anom_sun_rad) {



1633      rtb_T_ut1_J2000 -= floor(rtb_T_ut1_J2000 / mean_anom_sun_rad) *



1634        mean_anom_sun_rad;



1635    } else {



1636      rtb_T_ut1_J2000 /= mean_anom_sun_rad;



1637      if (fabs(rtb_T_ut1_J2000 - rt_roundd_snf(rtb_T_ut1_J2000)) <=



1638          2.2204460492503131E-16 * fabs(rtb_T_ut1_J2000)) {



1639        rtb_T_ut1_J2000 = 0.0;



1640      } else {

1642          mean_anom_sun_rad;



1643      }



1644    }



1645  }



1646



1647  rtb_T_ut1_J2000 /= 240.0;



1648



1649  /* '<S116>:1:123' GMST_1982 = deg2rad * mod(GMST_1982, 360); */



1650  rtb_T_ut1_J2000 = (rtb_T_ut1_J2000 - floor(rtb_T_ut1_J2000 / 360.0) * 360.0) *



1651    0.017453292519943295;



1652



1653  /* '<S116>:1:124' GAST_1982 = GMST_1982 + eqe_1980; */



1654  /*  Compute sidereal rotation */



1655  /*  GMST_1982 = asec2rad * (67310.54841 ... */



1656  /*                          + (876600 * 3600 + 8640184.812866) * jd_ut1_j2000_century ... */



1657  /*                          + 0.093104 * jd_ut1_j2000_century^2 ... */



1658  /*                          - 6.2e-6 * jd_ut1_j2000_century^3); */



1659  /*  GMST_1982 = mod(GMST_1982, 2*pi); */



1660  /*  GAST_1982 = GMST_1982 + eqe_1980; */



1661  /*  Compute rotation from pseudo-Earth fixed frame (does not include polar */



1662  /*  motion) */



1663  /* '<S116>:1:136' pef_to_tod = rot3(-GAST_1982); */



1664  rtb_T_ut1_J2000 = -(rtb_T_ut1_J2000 + rtb_T_TT_J2000);



1665



1666  /* '<S116>:1:157' y = [cos(u) sin(u) 0; -sin(u) cos(u) 0; 0 0 1]; */



1667  /*  % Compute polar motion (small angle approximation is assumed) */



1668  /*  itrf_to_pef = polar(polar_motion_rad(1), polar_motion_rad(2)); */



1669  /*  Compute composite rotations */



1670  /* '<S116>:1:142' teme_to_gcrf = mod_to_gcrf * tod_to_mod * teme_to_tod; */



1671  /* '<S116>:1:143' itrf_to_gcrf = mod_to_gcrf * tod_to_mod * pef_to_tod; */



1672  /*  * itrf_to_pef;   % for vecef */



1673  /* '<S116>:1:144' ppef_to_vgcrf = itrf_to_gcrf * skew([0; 0; o_prec]); */



1674  /*  for w x recef */



1675  rtb_MatrixMultiply[0] = cos(-rtb_T_TT_J2000);



1676  rtb_MatrixMultiply[3] = sin(-rtb_T_TT_J2000);



1677  rtb_MatrixMultiply[6] = 0.0;



1678  rtb_MatrixMultiply[1] = -sin(-rtb_T_TT_J2000);



1679  rtb_MatrixMultiply[4] = cos(-rtb_T_TT_J2000);



1680  rtb_MatrixMultiply[7] = 0.0;



1681  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {



1682    for (sigIdx = 0; sigIdx < 3; sigIdx++) {



1683      a_2[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] = 0.0;



1684      a_2[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] += tod_to_mod[3 * sigIdx] * rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2];



1685      a_2[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] += tod_to_mod[3 * sigIdx + 1] *



1686        rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2 + 3];



1687      a_2[idx2 + 3 * sigIdx] += tod_to_mod[3 * sigIdx + 2] *



1688        rtb_mod_to_gcrf[idx2 + 6];



1689    }



1690



1691    rtb_MatrixMultiply[2 + 3 * idx2] = d_0[idx2];



1692  }



1693



1694  for (idx2 = 0; idx2 < 3; idx2++) {



1695    for (sigIdx = 0; sigIdx < 3; sigIdx++) {



1696      rtb_teme_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] = 0.0;



1697      rtb_teme_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] += rtb_MatrixMultiply[3 * idx2] *



1698        a_2[sigIdx];



1699      rtb_teme_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] += rtb_MatrixMultiply[3 * idx2 + 1] *



1700        a_2[sigIdx + 3];



1701      rtb_teme_to_gcrf[sigIdx + 3 * idx2] += rtb_MatrixMultiply[3 * idx2 + 2] *



1702        a_2[sigIdx + 6];



1703    }



1704  }

1706  /* MATLAB Function: '<S65>/MATLAB Function' incorporates:



1707   *  Inport: '<Root>/orbit_tle'



1708   *  MATLAB Function: '<S115>/time-conversion-lib'



1709   */



1710  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1711  /*  LOAD CONSTANTS */



1712  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1713  /* MATLAB Function 'sgp4_lib_fsw/MATLAB Function': '<S111>:1' */



1714  /*  SGP4 Orbit Propagator */



1715  /*  UW Husky-Sat1 - ADCS Subsystem team */



1716  /*    Author:     Taylor Reynolds */



1717  /*    Updated:    7/3/18 */



1718  /*  Based on "SpaceTrack Report #3: Models for Propagation of NORAD Element */



1719  /*  Sets", Hoots & Roerhrich, 1980. */



1720  /*  */



1721  /*  TLE Format: */



1722  /*    Line 1: Column | Description */



1723  /*            01          line number of element data */



1724  /*            03-07       satellite number */



1725  /*            08          classification (u = unclassified) */



1726  /*            10-11       last two digits of launch year */



1727  /*            12-14       launch number of year */



1728  /*            15-17       piece of launch */



1729  /*            19-20       epoch year (last two digits) */



1730  /*            21-32       epoch (DOY and fractional portion of the day) */



1731  /*            34-43       first derivative of the mean motion */



1732  /*            45-52       second time derivative of mean motion (decimal */



1733  /*                            assumed) */



1734  /*            54-61       BS drag term (decimal point assumed) */



1735  /*            63          ephemeris type */



1736  /*            65-68       element number */



1737  /*            69          checksum (mod 10) */



1738  /*     */



1739  /*    Line 2: Column  | Description */



1740  /*            01          line number of element data */



1741  /*            03-07       satellite number */



1742  /*            09-16       inclination (degrees) */



1743  /*            18-25       right ascension of the ascending node (degrees) */



1744  /*            27-33       eccentricity (decimal assumed) */



1745  /*            35-42       argument of perigee (degrees) */



1746  /*            44-51       mean anomaly (degrees) */



1747  /*            53-63       mean motion (revs per day) */



1748  /*            64-68       revolution number at epoch (revs) */



1749  /*            69          checksum (mod 10) */



1750  /*  */



1751  /*  ----------------------------------------------------------------------- % */



1752  /*  Inputs: */



1753  /*    - orbit_tle: NORAD two line element set containing orbit info */



1754  /*    - tsince: Time since epoch of TLE in MINUTES */



1755  /*  Outputs: */



1756  /*    - pos_frame: Position vector in the TEME frame   */



1757  /*    - vel_frame: Velocity vector in the TEME frame */



1758  /*  */



1759  /*  Variables: */



1760  /*    - n_o = SGP type "mean" mean motion at epoch */



1761  /*    - e_o = the "mean" eccentricity at epoch */



1762  /*    - i_o = the "mean" inclination at epoch */



1763  /*    - M_o = the "mean" mean anomaly at epoch */



1764  /*    - w_o = the "mean" argument of perigee at epoch */



1765  /*    - Om_o = the "mean" longitude of ascending node at epoch */



1766  /*    - nd_o  = the TRoC of n_o */



1767  /*    - ndd_o = the TRoC of nd_o */



1768  /*    - Bs = the SGP4 type drag coefficient */



1769  /*    - k_e = gravitational constant of Earth, sqrt(GM_e) */



1770  /*    - a_E = the equatorial radius of Earth in ER */



1771  /*    - J_2 = the second gravitation zonal harmonic of Earth */



1772  /*    - J_3 = the third gravitational zonal harmonic of Earth */



1773  /*    - J_4 = the fourth gravitational zonal harmonic of Earth */



1774  /*    - (t-t_0) = time since epoch */



1775  /*    - k_2   = 0.5*J_2*a_E^2 */



1776  /*    - k_4   = -(3/8)*J_4*a_E^4 */



1777  /*    - A_30  = -J_3*a_E^3 */
